Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Member of Technical Staff 2* with *ThoughtSpot*. I bring over three years of professional experience building full-stack web applications, RAG pipelines, and AI agents, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade frontend and backend systems that directly reflect the full-stack technical depth and scalable system design this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I developed frontend and backend features for an MCP AI interaction layer that processes and manages customer data — translating natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints. I wrote clean, efficient, and testable code for generative developer tools (API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows), and architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph to enable scalable execution across distributed systems workflows. To keep these systems production-ready, I applied prompt routing and KV-cache optimizations that reduced end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS on an agile team — delivering full-stack features supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications, participating in code reviews, and helping improve system architecture. I also designed a cloud-agnostic scalable Storage Service in Python with PostgreSQL and Redis, applying Object-Oriented Design and database internals knowledge that directly maps to building reliable, high-performance platform systems at ThoughtSpot.

My academic and research background has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and collaborative technical practice — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and curiosity-driven culture ThoughtSpot values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full lifecycle of StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion model training, fine-tuning, and vLLM inference on a university HPC cluster, ensuring high performance and stability. Beyond building the systems, I led workshops on GPU programming and AI Agents using LangChain and LangGraph for 50+ students — an experience that sharpened my ability to communicate complex distributed systems concepts clearly and collaborate across knowledge levels. This combination of building production systems, conducting applied research, and daily integration of AI tools (Claude Code, Codex, and agentic coding pipelines) directly aligns with the AI literacy and adaptability ThoughtSpot requires of every Spotter.

I have always been passionate about making data accessible and actionable for everyone, and ThoughtSpot's mission to make the world more fact-driven by giving everyone faster, easier access to insights resonates deeply with the work I want to do. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

